description: Smallest integer whose name in colloquial American English (no "and"s) uses n different letters.
comments: Sequence stops at a(23) since 24,25,26 can't be achieved.
links: Michael Keith, Some properties of one, two, three..., Word Ways, 32:3 (1999), pp. 175-177.
example: a(5)=8 because "eight" is smallest number with 5 different letters.
author: Mike Keith (domnei(AT)aol.com)
